1
00:00:16,789 --> 00:00:18,123
[alarm beeps]

2
00:00:19,959 --> 00:00:22,211
[theme music playing]

3
00:00:58,706 --> 00:00:59,540
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

4
00:00:59,623 --> 00:01:01,125
CHILD ACTORS WERE FILMED SAFELY
WITH SUPERVISION

5
00:01:01,917 --> 00:01:03,878
[breezy music playing]

6
00:01:12,887 --> 00:01:14,722
[panting]

7
00:01:19,059 --> 00:01:22,229
[groaning]

8
00:01:23,397 --> 00:01:24,982
Is it too much for you?

9
00:01:25,065 --> 00:01:26,066
Yes.

10
00:01:30,779 --> 00:01:32,823
This is why you're getting tired
so quickly.

11
00:01:37,870 --> 00:01:38,913
This won't do.

12
00:01:40,497 --> 00:01:41,665
Let's run together more often.

13
00:01:44,084 --> 00:01:45,753
Give me a piggyback ride.

14
00:01:46,545 --> 00:01:47,546
[scoffs]

15
00:01:48,213 --> 00:01:49,506
[chuckles]

16
00:01:52,551 --> 00:01:54,219
-[Ji-yoon grunts]
-[Si-woo sighs]

17
00:01:54,303 --> 00:01:55,888
It's on you if my knees blow out.

18
00:01:56,388 --> 00:01:57,806
Ah, that's right.

19
00:01:57,890 --> 00:02:01,352
You said a fall at our age
can mean broken bones, right?

20
00:02:01,435 --> 00:02:03,646
Yeah, but you're obviously
not planning to get down.

21
00:02:04,813 --> 00:02:05,814
[sighs]

22
00:02:09,902 --> 00:02:12,071
[romantic music plays]

23
00:02:18,535 --> 00:02:20,537
[breezy music continues]

24
00:02:24,583 --> 00:02:25,584
[phone buzzes]

25
00:02:28,170 --> 00:02:29,713
[music fades]

26
00:02:29,797 --> 00:02:30,798
[phone buzzes]

27
00:02:34,176 --> 00:02:35,719
He left his cell phone here.

28
00:02:37,930 --> 00:02:39,181
[sighs]

29
00:02:41,558 --> 00:02:44,186
All right, then.
I'll reach out to him later.

30
00:02:55,364 --> 00:02:57,700
[Ji-yoon] No.
Don't do it, Cha Ji-yoon. Stop.

31
00:02:58,325 --> 00:02:59,451
[sighs]

32
00:02:59,535 --> 00:03:00,661
[taps feet]

33
00:03:01,453 --> 00:03:04,790
Yeah, why should
I demean myself like that?

34
00:03:04,873 --> 00:03:07,543
If I'm curious, I can just ask him. Hmm.

35
00:03:13,716 --> 00:03:15,884
But I ordered a soda, didn't I?

36
00:03:15,968 --> 00:03:17,219
[grunts]

37
00:03:17,302 --> 00:03:19,847
Sugary drinks after a workout
will make you thirstier.

38
00:03:19,930 --> 00:03:20,806
Drink water.

39
00:03:21,390 --> 00:03:23,851
[scoffs] Could you please respect
my taste too?

40
00:03:23,934 --> 00:03:26,061
I'll give in to everything else,
but not on your health.

41
00:03:26,645 --> 00:03:28,313
Are you really that worried I'll get sick?

42
00:03:28,397 --> 00:03:29,606
Yes.

43
00:03:29,690 --> 00:03:31,316
-Then I couldn't put you--
-Then you couldn't put me to work?

44
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,609
[laughs]

45
00:03:40,617 --> 00:03:42,661
Oh, your phone was ringing before.

46
00:03:58,844 --> 00:04:00,512
It's Senior Associate Lee.

47
00:04:00,596 --> 00:04:02,306
He says he'll be back at work next week.

48
00:04:03,057 --> 00:04:06,101
-[breezy music playing]
-I hope everything gets sorted out

49
00:04:06,185 --> 00:04:07,936
as soon as Mr. Lee comes back
to the office.

50
00:04:08,020 --> 00:04:09,354
Let's stay hopeful.

51
00:04:09,897 --> 00:04:12,274
He definitely has
the expertise to pull it off.

52
00:04:12,816 --> 00:04:14,151
Hmm.

53
00:04:14,234 --> 00:04:15,903
I'm a little jealous, though.

54
00:04:15,986 --> 00:04:16,987
Why?

55
00:04:17,071 --> 00:04:19,615
You'll always be my top pick,
Senior Associate Cha.

56
00:04:19,698 --> 00:04:20,991
[chuckles]

57
00:04:21,784 --> 00:04:23,077
When does practice finish today?

58
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,870
Hmm. Around 5:00.

59
00:04:25,537 --> 00:04:27,498
-I'll come pick you up.
-Okay.

60
00:04:29,833 --> 00:04:31,418
Okay, since you've rested enough,

61
00:04:32,044 --> 00:04:33,045
wanna run again?

62
00:04:33,128 --> 00:04:34,088
Again?

63
00:04:34,171 --> 00:04:35,172
Winner gets ice cream.

64
00:04:37,132 --> 00:04:38,550
[Ji-yoon yelps, chuckles]

65
00:04:41,178 --> 00:04:45,724
EPISODE 8 - HELD BACK
BY MY PAST, STILL CLOCKING IN!

66
00:04:45,808 --> 00:04:47,476
[music fades]

67
00:04:48,102 --> 00:04:49,103
[moans]

68
00:04:52,106 --> 00:04:53,357
Mmm!

69
00:04:53,941 --> 00:04:56,360
I knew it. Nothing beats young radish.

70
00:04:56,443 --> 00:04:58,529
Maybe just a touch more sesame oil?

71
00:04:58,612 --> 00:04:59,905
Well, that's new.

72
00:05:00,656 --> 00:05:03,742
You used to freak out
over having any kind of oil.

73
00:05:04,326 --> 00:05:06,745
Your little sister will start focusing

74
00:05:06,829 --> 00:05:09,206
on what she wants to do,
instead of what she shouldn't.

75
00:05:09,289 --> 00:05:10,499
Hmm.

76
00:05:10,582 --> 00:05:11,875
My little sister's all grown up.

77
00:05:11,959 --> 00:05:13,252
[phone buzzes]

78
00:05:15,254 --> 00:05:16,839
[Jae-in] Are you still mad at me?

79
00:05:18,382 --> 00:05:19,883
[sighs]

80
00:05:19,967 --> 00:05:22,052
-Why aren't you checking it?
-I don't need to.

81
00:05:23,887 --> 00:05:26,223
-Is it Kim Goo-won?
-[groans] No!

82
00:05:26,306 --> 00:05:27,516
Then why won't you check it? Let me see.

83
00:05:27,599 --> 00:05:29,685
[groans] I said it's not him!

84
00:05:29,768 --> 00:05:32,312
-"Hey No-ah, let's hang out."
-[groaning]

85
00:05:32,396 --> 00:05:34,565
-Give it back. Geez.
-"Are you still mad at me?"

86
00:05:34,648 --> 00:05:36,066
Just give it back already!

87
00:05:36,150 --> 00:05:38,610
Why would you read my text? Seriously.

88
00:05:38,694 --> 00:05:39,903
Who is this guy?

89
00:05:40,737 --> 00:05:43,866
Some guy who's just
as shallow as they come.

90
00:05:46,034 --> 00:05:47,035
[sighs]

91
00:05:47,119 --> 00:05:48,620
YOON NO-AH

92
00:05:51,582 --> 00:05:52,708
Seung-jun, am I shallow?

93
00:05:55,460 --> 00:05:57,754
[inhales sharply]
You are a bit of a lightweight.

94
00:05:59,214 --> 00:06:01,049
-Not physically.
-Why?

95
00:06:02,259 --> 00:06:04,094
Someone called you shallow?

96
00:06:04,178 --> 00:06:05,179
Mmm.

97
00:06:05,262 --> 00:06:07,681
[exhales deeply]
You're not exactly shallow.

98
00:06:08,849 --> 00:06:10,475
You've just never had to struggle
for anything.

99
00:06:10,559 --> 00:06:12,102
What does that mean?

100
00:06:12,186 --> 00:06:14,438
I mean that you've never had to pine
for anything.

101
00:06:15,022 --> 00:06:16,899
For an item, looks, or talent.

102
00:06:16,982 --> 00:06:18,150
Well, you're wrong.

103
00:06:18,233 --> 00:06:19,860
I want something so bad it's killing me.

104
00:06:19,943 --> 00:06:20,944
What?

105
00:06:22,362 --> 00:06:23,405
Muscles?

106
00:06:24,656 --> 00:06:25,908
-[sighs]
-[chuckles]

107
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:29,328
No-ah.

108
00:06:29,411 --> 00:06:30,454
No-ah?

109
00:06:31,330 --> 00:06:32,331
What's that?

110
00:06:34,124 --> 00:06:35,250
[Ga-eul] I'm off.

111
00:06:38,378 --> 00:06:39,546
Where are you going?

112
00:06:39,630 --> 00:06:40,797
Wedding song practice.

113
00:06:40,881 --> 00:06:42,090
You're singing at a wedding?

114
00:06:42,174 --> 00:06:43,342
Mm-hmm.

115
00:06:43,425 --> 00:06:46,470
I promised my college friends I'd do it,
so I want to keep my word.

116
00:06:46,553 --> 00:06:48,597
Come on, you're only doing it
'cause you get to see Ji-yoon.

117
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:50,140
It's not like that.

118
00:06:50,766 --> 00:06:51,767
It's over between us.

119
00:06:51,850 --> 00:06:54,186
Dude, so then why were your eyes glued
to Ji-yoon the whole time, huh?

120
00:06:54,269 --> 00:06:55,562
[scoffs]

121
00:06:55,646 --> 00:06:56,647
Were they?

122
00:06:58,148 --> 00:06:59,775
I should be more careful.

123
00:06:59,858 --> 00:07:01,485
She must've felt uncomfortable.

124
00:07:02,945 --> 00:07:04,071
Later.

125
00:07:04,571 --> 00:07:05,572
[Jae-in] Bye.

126
00:07:06,114 --> 00:07:07,115
See ya.

127
00:07:11,328 --> 00:07:12,996
[sighs heavily]

128
00:07:13,705 --> 00:07:15,666
Do I make No-ah uncomfortable too?

129
00:07:19,795 --> 00:07:20,796
Hye-ji.

130
00:07:22,005 --> 00:07:24,341
Hmm? What?

131
00:07:26,134 --> 00:07:27,219
What is it?

132
00:07:28,679 --> 00:07:31,390
Well, Mr. Kang and I…

133
00:07:32,724 --> 00:07:33,809
we're dating.

134
00:07:35,143 --> 00:07:36,478
You said you wouldn't.

135
00:07:37,062 --> 00:07:38,105
You told me not to worry.

136
00:07:38,188 --> 00:07:40,816
I know. It just turned out that way.

137
00:07:40,899 --> 00:07:43,110
You said his ex-wife was your mentor.

138
00:07:43,193 --> 00:07:45,404
You're gonna keep
running into her at work.

139
00:07:45,487 --> 00:07:46,822
You really want to deal with that?

140
00:07:46,905 --> 00:07:50,033
To be honest, it really bothers me.

141
00:07:50,867 --> 00:07:54,121
Seeing them at work together
ruins my mood for no reason.

142
00:07:54,204 --> 00:07:55,956
Think about what comes next, please.

143
00:07:56,540 --> 00:07:57,749
Getting married means

144
00:07:58,250 --> 00:07:59,584
becoming a family.

145
00:07:59,668 --> 00:08:02,045
It's something
you haven't experienced yet.

146
00:08:02,129 --> 00:08:03,547
It's a lot harder than you think,

147
00:08:03,630 --> 00:08:07,301
and there'll be so much for you
to accept and understand.

148
00:08:08,552 --> 00:08:11,430
I understand. I guess you're right.

149
00:08:12,139 --> 00:08:13,515
You're smiling?

150
00:08:13,598 --> 00:08:14,808
Hey…

151
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:19,062
I'm honestly so happy these days Hye-ji.

152
00:08:19,146 --> 00:08:20,147
[groans]

153
00:08:22,107 --> 00:08:23,817
[groans] You're driving me nuts.

154
00:08:24,443 --> 00:08:25,777
[sighs] Whatever. Fine.

155
00:08:25,861 --> 00:08:28,655
You've already made up your mind,
so I can't stop you now.

156
00:08:28,739 --> 00:08:30,907
So please stop worrying so much,

157
00:08:30,991 --> 00:08:32,784
and show me some support.

158
00:08:32,868 --> 00:08:34,619
[sighs heavily]

159
00:08:34,703 --> 00:08:37,539
Then just bring him to the wedding,
so I can at least see his face.

160
00:08:37,622 --> 00:08:38,623
[chuckles]

161
00:08:39,583 --> 00:08:41,752
You know, he's super good-looking.

162
00:08:42,294 --> 00:08:43,670
I know.

163
00:08:43,754 --> 00:08:44,796
How would you know that?

164
00:08:44,880 --> 00:08:46,089
You only go for a pretty face.

165
00:08:46,173 --> 00:08:47,382
-[scoffs]
-[scoffs]

166
00:08:47,466 --> 00:08:48,592
-Geez!
-[scoffs]

167
00:08:49,718 --> 00:08:50,761
Yeah, I do.

168
00:08:56,892 --> 00:08:57,893
[sighs]

169
00:08:58,602 --> 00:08:59,603
Ji-yoon!

170
00:09:03,065 --> 00:09:05,067
Come with us.
We're all having dinner together.

171
00:09:05,776 --> 00:09:06,777
I have plans.

172
00:09:07,361 --> 00:09:09,321
Can't you just relax around me?

173
00:09:10,405 --> 00:09:11,406
Like with Seung-jun.

174
00:09:11,490 --> 00:09:13,617
Just treat me like an old college friend.

175
00:09:14,201 --> 00:09:16,328
I told you that I--

176
00:09:16,411 --> 00:09:17,245
Ji-yoon.

177
00:09:20,665 --> 00:09:21,875
Mr. Kang.

178
00:09:29,091 --> 00:09:30,384
We meet again.

179
00:09:32,427 --> 00:09:33,678
I'm Kang Si-woo.

180
00:09:33,762 --> 00:09:35,555
KANG SI-WOO
MANAGER

181
00:09:36,306 --> 00:09:39,643
Oh, you're Ji-yoon's boss
from back then, right?

182
00:09:41,478 --> 00:09:42,479
Hello.

183
00:09:43,397 --> 00:09:45,440
But what brings you here?

184
00:09:46,024 --> 00:09:48,193
Mr. Kang, let's go.

185
00:10:01,998 --> 00:10:02,999
Ji-yoon.

186
00:10:03,583 --> 00:10:06,128
-I didn't mean to keep it from you.
-[Si-woo] No.

187
00:10:06,711 --> 00:10:08,505
I feel like I interrupted you two.

188
00:10:09,005 --> 00:10:10,882
If you need to talk more, please go ahead.

189
00:10:14,594 --> 00:10:16,263
Go on now. I'll wait here.

190
00:10:18,682 --> 00:10:21,351
Then I'll just be a minute, okay?

191
00:10:32,279 --> 00:10:34,656
Ji-yoon, what's going on? Why is he…

192
00:10:34,739 --> 00:10:36,408
He's my boyfriend, Ga-eul.

193
00:10:37,826 --> 00:10:38,827
What?

194
00:10:43,957 --> 00:10:44,958
Since when, though?

195
00:10:45,041 --> 00:10:46,668
It hasn't been long.

196
00:10:47,252 --> 00:10:51,256
So I'd appreciate it
if you didn't contact me anymore, please.

197
00:10:53,049 --> 00:10:55,218
[breathes deeply]
I'll see you at the wedding.

198
00:10:57,471 --> 00:10:58,472
[sighs]

199
00:11:09,900 --> 00:11:11,234
I regretted it immediately.

200
00:11:12,444 --> 00:11:13,445
Thank you so much.

201
00:11:13,528 --> 00:11:16,031
[peaceful music playing]

202
00:11:20,744 --> 00:11:22,871
I'm really sorry I didn't tell you sooner.

203
00:11:23,622 --> 00:11:25,415
He joined so suddenly.

204
00:11:26,249 --> 00:11:28,084
And I didn't want you to worry
over nothing.

205
00:11:28,793 --> 00:11:32,464
I saw Cho Ga-eul walking in
when I dropped you off last time.

206
00:11:33,048 --> 00:11:34,382
And why didn't you say anything?

207
00:11:35,008 --> 00:11:37,093
I was waiting for you
to bring it up first.

208
00:11:38,011 --> 00:11:39,012
Oh.

209
00:11:40,180 --> 00:11:44,100
So is this how it feels for you
when you see me with Ms. Choi

210
00:11:44,184 --> 00:11:45,519
at the office?

211
00:11:46,228 --> 00:11:47,437
How does it feel?

212
00:11:48,355 --> 00:11:50,065
I know there's nothing between you two,

213
00:11:50,774 --> 00:11:51,858
but it still bothers me.

214
00:11:53,276 --> 00:11:54,277
Yeah.

215
00:11:55,779 --> 00:11:58,532
Things between her and me ended
a very long time ago.

216
00:11:58,615 --> 00:12:00,700
I don't have any feelings left for her.

217
00:12:00,784 --> 00:12:02,369
I feel the same way.

218
00:12:03,078 --> 00:12:06,248
I just hope he has a good life.

219
00:12:07,791 --> 00:12:08,792
Right.

220
00:12:11,002 --> 00:12:14,130
Oh, my friend, Hye-ji, told me
to bring you to her wedding.

221
00:12:14,631 --> 00:12:17,217
Does that mean
I finally get to see your drum skills?

222
00:12:17,300 --> 00:12:18,134
Yes.

223
00:12:18,218 --> 00:12:19,386
Then I can't miss it.

224
00:12:19,886 --> 00:12:21,513
So I better practice harder.

225
00:12:22,806 --> 00:12:24,516
-[mellow music playing on speakers]
-[Hye-ji sighs]

226
00:12:24,599 --> 00:12:26,560
Must've been a shock running into them.

227
00:12:27,852 --> 00:12:28,853
It's weird, right?

228
00:12:29,854 --> 00:12:32,274
Why did it never even occur to me that

229
00:12:33,149 --> 00:12:35,318
there could be someone else
by Ji-yoon's side?

230
00:12:35,402 --> 00:12:38,363
Well, that's because
you've never had to experience it.

231
00:12:38,446 --> 00:12:41,908
She liked you all throughout college,
she wouldn't even look at anyone else.

232
00:12:41,992 --> 00:12:44,077
[Hye-ji] Yeah, you have to accept it now.

233
00:12:44,661 --> 00:12:46,121
-[sighs]
-[Seung-jun sighs]

234
00:12:46,705 --> 00:12:49,165
Hey, back in college,
you knew how she felt,

235
00:12:49,249 --> 00:12:51,042
so why did you pretend you didn't notice?

236
00:12:53,003 --> 00:12:55,213
'Cause I wanted her to stay in my life.

237
00:12:56,047 --> 00:13:00,385
I was scared that if we dated
and then broke up,

238
00:13:00,468 --> 00:13:01,845
we'd lose our friendship.

239
00:13:03,013 --> 00:13:04,139
Well,

240
00:13:05,390 --> 00:13:07,058
I guess that's how things ended.

241
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:13,148
[Hye-ji sighs] Listen, Ga-eul,

242
00:13:13,231 --> 00:13:16,067
you just need to keep thriving
like you are now.

243
00:13:16,151 --> 00:13:18,194
That's what's best for Ji-yoon too.

244
00:13:18,278 --> 00:13:20,572
She already has a lot on her mind,

245
00:13:20,655 --> 00:13:22,532
so don't make things harder for her.

246
00:13:24,409 --> 00:13:25,410
What do you mean?

247
00:13:26,786 --> 00:13:28,371
Is something going on with her?

248
00:13:29,205 --> 00:13:30,332
No.

249
00:13:30,415 --> 00:13:33,668
I mean, we all have a lot on our minds.

250
00:13:33,752 --> 00:13:35,337
You, me, and Seung-jun too.

251
00:13:35,420 --> 00:13:36,421
No, not me.

252
00:13:36,504 --> 00:13:37,922
What is it?

253
00:13:38,006 --> 00:13:40,383
Tell me. Something's up with her, right?

254
00:13:40,467 --> 00:13:41,801
No, no, no, no.

255
00:13:41,885 --> 00:13:43,094
Come on, spill it!

256
00:13:47,682 --> 00:13:50,769
Hello. I am the newest member
of the task force, Lee Young-hun.

257
00:13:50,852 --> 00:13:52,771
-[Kee-tae] Nice to meet you.
-[Na-ri] Nice to meet you!

258
00:13:52,854 --> 00:13:54,105
Welcome to the team, Mr. Lee.

259
00:13:54,189 --> 00:13:55,106
Thanks.

260
00:13:55,190 --> 00:13:57,859
We can skip the pleasantries.
Let's all get to work.

261
00:13:57,942 --> 00:13:58,985
Should I book a meeting room?

262
00:13:59,069 --> 00:14:01,696
No need. We'll be heading
to the product showroom today.

263
00:14:02,906 --> 00:14:05,325
-[Na-ri] The product showroom?
-[Kee-tae] Let's go.

264
00:14:05,408 --> 00:14:07,410
[futuristic music playing]

265
00:14:13,124 --> 00:14:14,501
Whoa.

266
00:14:14,584 --> 00:14:15,960
What is all this?

267
00:14:16,044 --> 00:14:18,546
We'll start using this space
as our Home-AI Lab now.

268
00:14:18,630 --> 00:14:22,092
This is where we'll test inter-device
connectivity and the AI experience.

269
00:14:22,175 --> 00:14:25,679
[chuckling] No way.
It's nicer than my home.

270
00:14:25,762 --> 00:14:27,263
[secretary] The President is here.

271
00:14:27,347 --> 00:14:30,016
-President Han? Oh! Oh, gosh…
-[Na-ri stammers]

272
00:14:30,725 --> 00:14:31,726
Hello.

273
00:14:31,810 --> 00:14:33,812
[U-jin chuckles]

274
00:14:33,895 --> 00:14:36,398
Seeing you freeze up
makes me feel like an unwelcome guest.

275
00:14:36,481 --> 00:14:38,149
Please, you can relax.

276
00:14:38,233 --> 00:14:39,693
-Yes, ma'am.
-[U-jin chuckles softly]

277
00:14:39,776 --> 00:14:40,985
Uh…

278
00:14:41,486 --> 00:14:42,821
Well, the upcoming demo

279
00:14:42,904 --> 00:14:45,949
will be held right here
in the product showroom.

280
00:14:46,032 --> 00:14:47,409
Given the nature of this project,

281
00:14:47,492 --> 00:14:49,661
I felt a more private setting
would be appropriate,

282
00:14:49,744 --> 00:14:51,579
which is why we chose this space.

283
00:14:51,663 --> 00:14:53,581
Just trust Manager Kang Si-woo
and follow his lead.

284
00:14:53,665 --> 00:14:54,499
[Kee-tae] Yes, ma'am.

285
00:14:54,582 --> 00:14:55,458
[U-jin] So,

286
00:14:55,542 --> 00:14:58,878
that being said,
be extra vigilant about security.

287
00:14:58,962 --> 00:15:01,589
It would be a shame to have your hard work
stolen by someone else,

288
00:15:01,673 --> 00:15:02,924
-wouldn't it?
-[Kee-tae] Yes, ma'am.

289
00:15:03,007 --> 00:15:06,261
All right, then.
I'll look forward to a stellar demo.

290
00:15:08,346 --> 00:15:09,347
Ah…

291
00:15:10,432 --> 00:15:12,976
You did the new product release
presentation, right?

292
00:15:13,059 --> 00:15:15,228
Yes. I'm Senior Associate Cha Ji-yoon.

293
00:15:15,311 --> 00:15:18,273
All right.
I'm also counting on you for this demo.

294
00:15:18,356 --> 00:15:19,190
Sure.

295
00:15:19,816 --> 00:15:20,900
All right, then.

296
00:15:22,360 --> 00:15:23,361
Thank you, ma'am.

297
00:15:26,114 --> 00:15:28,700
[music fades]

298
00:15:31,369 --> 00:15:33,329
You look like you have a lot of questions.

299
00:15:33,413 --> 00:15:35,373
Is there anything else we don't know?

300
00:15:35,457 --> 00:15:36,666
Yes.

301
00:15:36,750 --> 00:15:39,794
So, you're going to keep
dropping surprises on us?

302
00:15:39,878 --> 00:15:41,546
-Yes.
-But why?

303
00:15:41,629 --> 00:15:43,840
Because, like the President said,
security is key.

304
00:15:49,804 --> 00:15:50,805
[chuckles]

305
00:15:52,807 --> 00:15:54,267
[Young-hun sighs]

306
00:15:55,143 --> 00:15:56,811
[inhales sharply]
With this kind of approach,

307
00:15:56,895 --> 00:15:58,855
even ten cameras
won't really work, you know?

308
00:15:58,938 --> 00:16:00,940
Then what should we do?

309
00:16:02,358 --> 00:16:03,359
Well, how about this?

310
00:16:03,443 --> 00:16:06,070
-[dynamic music playing]
-Say you reach in with an ingredient

311
00:16:06,821 --> 00:16:08,364
and pull your hand out empty.

312
00:16:08,448 --> 00:16:11,201
Or the opposite, you reach in empty-handed

313
00:16:12,660 --> 00:16:14,245
and bring it out holding an ingredient.

314
00:16:14,329 --> 00:16:16,206
We can teach it these actions patterns

315
00:16:16,289 --> 00:16:18,625
to track exactly what's coming in
and out of the refrigerator.

316
00:16:18,708 --> 00:16:22,504
Then it can identify
the specific ingredient too, right?

317
00:16:22,587 --> 00:16:23,588
Of course.

318
00:16:23,671 --> 00:16:25,590
It'll recognize
whether you're putting in or taking out

319
00:16:25,673 --> 00:16:27,717
a banana, an apple, or broccoli,

320
00:16:27,801 --> 00:16:29,803
and it will even generate
an inventory list.

321
00:16:29,886 --> 00:16:31,888
And it can also recommend
dishes and recipes

322
00:16:31,971 --> 00:16:33,807
based on what's
in the refrigerator, right?

323
00:16:33,890 --> 00:16:35,016
Yes.

324
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:36,935
Amazing.

325
00:16:37,018 --> 00:16:38,853
However… Hmm…

326
00:16:38,937 --> 00:16:41,314
We will probably have to switch
to a better camera.

327
00:16:41,981 --> 00:16:43,191
Right.

328
00:16:43,274 --> 00:16:44,984
-[Kee-tae] Mr. Young-hun.
-Yes?

329
00:16:45,068 --> 00:16:46,319
Could you take a look at this?

330
00:16:46,402 --> 00:16:47,987
Ah. Give me a moment.

331
00:16:53,409 --> 00:16:55,078
Looks like things are going well.

332
00:16:55,662 --> 00:16:56,871
Yes.

333
00:16:56,955 --> 00:17:00,083
I think Mr. Young-hun
is totally our relief pitcher.

334
00:17:03,586 --> 00:17:04,879
[chuckles]

335
00:17:07,298 --> 00:17:09,884
[music fades]

336
00:17:09,968 --> 00:17:12,595
[Ji-yoon] Someone has to crack this
once and for all.

337
00:17:12,679 --> 00:17:15,932
It's basically a race to see
who lands on the moon first.

338
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:20,186
[sighs]

339
00:17:20,270 --> 00:17:21,271
[door opens]

340
00:17:21,354 --> 00:17:22,772
It's the new version. That's interesting.

341
00:17:22,856 --> 00:17:24,148
[No-ah] You're here.

342
00:17:24,232 --> 00:17:26,150
Oh, sit, sit, sit. Thank you.

343
00:17:27,902 --> 00:17:29,821
-Have you been waiting long?
-[No-ah] Not at all.

344
00:17:29,904 --> 00:17:31,406
What did you want to ask me?

345
00:17:31,489 --> 00:17:34,158
It's about the remote-controlled
induction cooktop.

346
00:17:34,242 --> 00:17:35,618
I would like to revisit it.

347
00:17:35,702 --> 00:17:38,329
Well, I told you, we can't do that.

348
00:17:38,413 --> 00:17:41,583
It is, uh, specifically written
into the regulations.

349
00:17:42,250 --> 00:17:45,128
And what if we use a regulatory sandbox?

350
00:17:45,628 --> 00:17:48,715
If the results are good,
it just might change the regulations.

351
00:17:48,798 --> 00:17:51,217
-[upbeat music playing]
-That's right. A regulatory…

352
00:17:51,301 --> 00:17:52,552
A SYSTEM GRANTING TEMPORARY EXEMPTIONS
FOR MARKET TESTING OF NEW TECHNOLOGY

353
00:17:52,635 --> 00:17:54,762
Wait, how'd you come up with that? Wow.

354
00:17:55,346 --> 00:17:56,973
I'm seeing you in a whole new light now.

355
00:17:57,056 --> 00:17:57,932
Thank you, sir.

356
00:17:58,016 --> 00:17:59,893
Apply for the regulatory sandbox.

357
00:17:59,976 --> 00:18:01,352
And let's do this together.

358
00:18:01,436 --> 00:18:04,022
Yes! [chuckles]

359
00:18:04,105 --> 00:18:06,107
-[sighs]
-[phone buzzes]

360
00:18:10,069 --> 00:18:12,071
[music fades]

361
00:18:12,155 --> 00:18:13,573
[person] Is this No-ah's number?

362
00:18:13,656 --> 00:18:16,034
I'm Jae-in's girlfriend.
We met the other day.

363
00:18:16,117 --> 00:18:17,118
Can we meet?

364
00:18:17,201 --> 00:18:18,202
[scoffs]

365
00:18:19,787 --> 00:18:20,788
Wow.

366
00:18:21,456 --> 00:18:24,584
I didn't see this twist coming at all.

367
00:18:30,632 --> 00:18:32,508
-Oh, thank you.
-Sure.

368
00:18:35,136 --> 00:18:36,346
Oh, yeah. Thanks.

369
00:18:36,429 --> 00:18:37,555
-Yeah.
-[Young-hun] Here.

370
00:18:39,349 --> 00:18:41,476
-Oh, thank you.
-[Kee-tae] Here you go, Mr. Lee.

371
00:18:41,559 --> 00:18:42,518
[chuckles]

372
00:18:43,394 --> 00:18:44,228
Hmm.

373
00:18:46,856 --> 00:18:48,983
-Yeah, it is good. [chuckles]
-[Young-hun] Ah, thanks.

374
00:18:54,822 --> 00:18:55,907
[Na-ri sighs]

375
00:18:58,201 --> 00:18:59,285
This one's yours.

376
00:19:01,579 --> 00:19:03,373
-Here you go.
-Ah, yes. Thank you.

377
00:19:03,915 --> 00:19:05,041
[Na-ri] Thank you.

378
00:19:07,418 --> 00:19:08,419
Thank you.

379
00:19:09,212 --> 00:19:11,881
Mr. Kang, you've changed a lot
since I last saw you.

380
00:19:13,633 --> 00:19:14,968
[server] Here's your order.

381
00:19:15,051 --> 00:19:16,636
-[Kee-tae] Wow. It's kimchi stew.
-Looks delicious.

382
00:19:16,719 --> 00:19:18,179
-[Kee-tae] Kimchi stew.
-Thank you.

383
00:19:18,262 --> 00:19:19,639
[Kee-tae, Na-ri] Thank you!

384
00:19:23,810 --> 00:19:26,062
-[Young-hun] Enjoy your meal.
-[Kee-tae] Enjoy your meal.

385
00:19:36,239 --> 00:19:37,573
[sighs]

386
00:19:37,657 --> 00:19:38,908
What? Wh-What is it?

387
00:19:38,992 --> 00:19:41,035
-What did I do? What? Tell me.
-[awkward music playing]

388
00:19:41,119 --> 00:19:42,662
-What?
-That wasn't you?

389
00:19:42,745 --> 00:19:43,871
Was what?

390
00:19:45,123 --> 00:19:47,166
Oh, I'm sorry, sir. Right. [clears throat]

391
00:19:54,674 --> 00:19:55,675
Wow, Mr. Kang.

392
00:19:56,676 --> 00:19:58,052
Uh, if you keep doing this…

393
00:19:59,220 --> 00:20:00,138
[stammers]

394
00:20:02,056 --> 00:20:03,307
[clears throat]

395
00:20:03,891 --> 00:20:05,143
If you do this for me too,

396
00:20:05,727 --> 00:20:06,894
that's true love right there.

397
00:20:08,021 --> 00:20:09,856
-[chuckles]
-[chuckles]

398
00:20:12,942 --> 00:20:15,236
The thing is,
you're not at that level yet.

399
00:20:15,319 --> 00:20:16,612
-[Young-hun chuckles]
-I'm sorry, sir.

400
00:20:16,696 --> 00:20:18,698
[task force members chuckling]

401
00:20:18,781 --> 00:20:20,074
[Young-hun] Want me
to peel that apart for you?

402
00:20:20,158 --> 00:20:21,492
[Kee-tae] Hey, now I'm offended.

403
00:20:21,576 --> 00:20:23,161
-[chuckling] I'm just kidding.
-[Young-hun] All right.

404
00:20:23,244 --> 00:20:24,412
You should know that I'm married.

405
00:20:24,495 --> 00:20:26,164
-[Kee-tae] So am I.
-[Young-hun] Oh, I see.

406
00:20:26,247 --> 00:20:27,749
[music ends]

407
00:20:30,001 --> 00:20:31,002
And where is Mr. Lee?

408
00:20:31,085 --> 00:20:32,378
R&D building.

409
00:20:33,588 --> 00:20:35,590
-[elevator chimes]
-[sighs]

410
00:20:39,886 --> 00:20:42,013
Uh, excuse me. We're getting off.

411
00:20:42,513 --> 00:20:43,723
Excuse us, please.

412
00:20:44,348 --> 00:20:46,851
[rock music playing]

413
00:20:49,145 --> 00:20:50,688
Oh. Oh? Whoa, hey!

414
00:20:50,772 --> 00:20:52,356
[task force members exclaiming]

415
00:20:55,943 --> 00:20:57,653
-[gasps]
-[chuckles]

416
00:20:57,737 --> 00:20:58,613
[gasps]

417
00:20:59,447 --> 00:21:02,325
Looks like we're really
becoming a team, Mr. Kang!

418
00:21:02,408 --> 00:21:05,203
Well, anyway,
I'll be eating alone tomorrow.

419
00:21:05,286 --> 00:21:08,039
No! We were just starting to bond!
You have to eat with us.

420
00:21:08,122 --> 00:21:09,832
-[chuckling]
-Aw. Come on, Mr. Kang!

421
00:21:13,461 --> 00:21:15,963
[music ends]

422
00:21:22,011 --> 00:21:25,139
-[tranquil music playing on speakers]
-[No-ah sighs]

423
00:21:25,223 --> 00:21:27,809
Sorry for making you come all this way.

424
00:21:27,892 --> 00:21:29,644
It's just that I'm still on the clock.

425
00:21:29,727 --> 00:21:32,480
It's okay.
I'm the one who asked to see you.

426
00:21:32,563 --> 00:21:33,648
Why did you want to see me?

427
00:21:34,232 --> 00:21:35,983
Well, I could ask you the same thing.

428
00:21:36,484 --> 00:21:39,403
Honestly, you could've
just ignored my text.

429
00:21:39,987 --> 00:21:43,282
I figured meeting up
would at least ease your mind a bit.

430
00:21:46,577 --> 00:21:48,830
I was the one who suggested we break up.

431
00:21:50,957 --> 00:21:53,709
My ego took a hit
because it felt like Jae-in

432
00:21:53,793 --> 00:21:55,211
didn't really like me that much.

433
00:21:56,504 --> 00:22:00,258
I thought if I suggested we break up,
Jae-in would beg me to stay with him.

434
00:22:00,842 --> 00:22:02,176
But he didn't do that.

435
00:22:03,803 --> 00:22:05,054
Instead, he said,

436
00:22:05,888 --> 00:22:09,433
"Okay. What can we do
if the feelings aren't there anymore?"

437
00:22:13,229 --> 00:22:15,314
The feelings weren't there anymore.

438
00:22:16,649 --> 00:22:18,609
So it wasn't Jae-in

439
00:22:19,443 --> 00:22:21,112
who no longer had feelings?

440
00:22:21,696 --> 00:22:24,740
He might look like a player,
but he's sincere deep down.

441
00:22:24,824 --> 00:22:26,492
He might seem to do whatever he wants,

442
00:22:26,993 --> 00:22:28,327
but he never lies.

443
00:22:29,078 --> 00:22:30,079
[No-ah sighs]

444
00:22:30,163 --> 00:22:31,956
I know it wasn't because of you.

445
00:22:32,915 --> 00:22:35,501
To be honest, our relationship

446
00:22:35,585 --> 00:22:37,920
was practically over a long time ago.

447
00:22:39,630 --> 00:22:42,008
You came all this way
just to tell me that?

448
00:22:42,091 --> 00:22:45,219
You could've just looked the other way,
you know?

449
00:22:45,803 --> 00:22:46,846
The moment

450
00:22:47,346 --> 00:22:49,932
I saw Jae-in run out after you that day,

451
00:22:50,516 --> 00:22:52,435
I realized he must really like you.

452
00:22:53,102 --> 00:22:55,521
I've never seen him do
anything like that before.

453
00:22:55,605 --> 00:22:57,023
[emotional music playing]

454
00:22:57,106 --> 00:22:59,942
Whether you accept him or not
is entirely up to you,

455
00:23:00,443 --> 00:23:02,403
but I didn't want you
to get the wrong idea.

456
00:23:03,237 --> 00:23:06,240
Besides, I have no intention
of going back with him.

457
00:23:08,618 --> 00:23:09,911
And that's really all.

458
00:23:12,580 --> 00:23:13,623
[exhales sharply]

459
00:23:16,250 --> 00:23:18,127
[music fades]

460
00:23:18,211 --> 00:23:20,379
I guess I'll just wait here a bit.

461
00:23:23,716 --> 00:23:26,010
Huh? Why is he…

462
00:23:27,303 --> 00:23:29,805
[dramatic music playing]

463
00:23:43,861 --> 00:23:44,862
[sighs]

464
00:23:54,413 --> 00:23:57,083
-[music continues]
-[no audible dialogue]

465
00:24:43,212 --> 00:24:44,797
[exhales deeply]

466
00:24:47,508 --> 00:24:49,510
[music fades]

467
00:24:50,511 --> 00:24:51,512
[sighs]

468
00:24:52,388 --> 00:24:54,640
I ran into some people from the office

469
00:24:54,724 --> 00:24:55,850
on the way here.

470
00:24:57,518 --> 00:24:59,979
And did you run into anyone also?

471
00:25:00,896 --> 00:25:01,897
No.

472
00:25:02,898 --> 00:25:03,899
Ah.

473
00:25:03,983 --> 00:25:05,151
Thank goodness.

474
00:25:05,776 --> 00:25:06,861
You said Seochon, right?

475
00:25:07,570 --> 00:25:08,571
Yes.

476
00:25:11,449 --> 00:25:13,075
You must've been really on edge,

477
00:25:13,659 --> 00:25:15,202
forgetting your seat belt like this.

478
00:25:16,370 --> 00:25:17,580
Yes, I guess I was.

479
00:25:18,789 --> 00:25:20,082
Well, let's get going.

480
00:25:28,549 --> 00:25:30,676
-[brother] ♪ Happy birthday to you ♪
-[clapping]

481
00:25:30,760 --> 00:25:32,845
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

482
00:25:32,928 --> 00:25:36,182
♪ Happy birthday, dear Mom ♪

483
00:25:36,265 --> 00:25:38,017
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

484
00:25:38,100 --> 00:25:39,602
[exclaims]

485
00:25:40,102 --> 00:25:42,730
[gentle music playing on speakers]

486
00:25:44,440 --> 00:25:45,691
Happy birthday, Mom.

487
00:25:45,775 --> 00:25:47,651
Oh, and I bought the cake for you.

488
00:25:48,152 --> 00:25:49,695
-Thank you, son. Thanks.
-[chuckles]

489
00:25:49,779 --> 00:25:51,906
Lady Nam Hye-gyeong…

490
00:25:53,366 --> 00:25:54,950
Happy birthday, Mom.

491
00:25:55,034 --> 00:25:56,285
Thank you, honey.

492
00:25:56,369 --> 00:25:57,620
I'll put it to good use.

493
00:25:59,330 --> 00:26:00,956
Dad, you should say something too.

494
00:26:01,040 --> 00:26:02,208
[Yeong-mook] Mm-hmm.

495
00:26:02,291 --> 00:26:03,584
Happy birthday.

496
00:26:04,585 --> 00:26:07,046
You're empty-handed yet again this year.

497
00:26:11,592 --> 00:26:13,886
Well, I'm footing the bill.

498
00:26:14,595 --> 00:26:17,390
We've done it this way every year.
It's nothing new.

499
00:26:17,473 --> 00:26:18,599
-Mmm.
-[Yeong-mook] Mmm.

500
00:26:19,183 --> 00:26:22,311
Eating a meal with you
is basically an annual event now.

501
00:26:23,354 --> 00:26:25,272
[sighs, clears throat]

502
00:26:25,898 --> 00:26:27,441
[server] Please, excuse me.

503
00:26:30,736 --> 00:26:31,946
Enjoy your meal.

504
00:26:32,738 --> 00:26:34,323
Wow, looks good.

505
00:26:34,407 --> 00:26:36,575
-Doesn't it, Mom?
-Yes. Let's eat.

506
00:26:36,659 --> 00:26:38,035
Yeah, eat up.

507
00:26:39,870 --> 00:26:42,373
[combative music playing]

508
00:26:46,293 --> 00:26:47,545
[Yeong-mook grunts]

509
00:27:04,770 --> 00:27:07,440
-[music ends]
-What? You like sweet and sour pork.

510
00:27:07,523 --> 00:27:09,400
[chuckles]

511
00:27:10,276 --> 00:27:12,945
That was only what I craved
while I was pregnant

512
00:27:13,028 --> 00:27:14,321
with Joon-su.

513
00:27:16,115 --> 00:27:18,617
I like stir-fried seafood
and Chinese meatballs too.

514
00:27:25,124 --> 00:27:26,459
[carousel turns]

515
00:27:30,045 --> 00:27:31,172
[sighs]

516
00:27:31,755 --> 00:27:32,715
[Yeong-mook sniffs]

517
00:27:32,798 --> 00:27:34,925
But how would you know what I like anyway?

518
00:27:35,009 --> 00:27:36,844
You might as well be a stranger.
I barely see you.

519
00:27:36,927 --> 00:27:38,053
Hey, Mom.

520
00:27:38,137 --> 00:27:40,431
If you have something to say, say it.
I'm listening.

521
00:27:40,514 --> 00:27:41,515
Fine.

522
00:27:42,725 --> 00:27:44,477
Well… [sighs]

523
00:27:44,560 --> 00:27:46,437
When I kicked you up to the attic
in a fit of anger,

524
00:27:46,520 --> 00:27:48,230
you went up there
like you'd been waiting for it.

525
00:27:48,314 --> 00:27:49,982
You said you couldn't sleep.

526
00:27:50,065 --> 00:27:52,109
So I did it so you could
sleep comfortably.

527
00:27:52,193 --> 00:27:53,569
Then you could've come home early

528
00:27:53,652 --> 00:27:55,571
instead of coming in late
and rustling around!

529
00:27:55,654 --> 00:27:58,365
Do you honestly think I called you
because I was scared

530
00:27:58,449 --> 00:27:59,575
of bugs or burglars?

531
00:27:59,658 --> 00:28:02,495
Who on earth comes home
only to head right back out?

532
00:28:02,578 --> 00:28:03,954
And you think buying dinner is enough?

533
00:28:04,038 --> 00:28:06,290
How can you come empty-handed
this year again!

534
00:28:06,373 --> 00:28:07,875
Okay, well…

535
00:28:08,375 --> 00:28:10,169
Is there something that you want?

536
00:28:19,720 --> 00:28:20,804
What is this?

537
00:28:25,142 --> 00:28:27,520
MARRIAGE GRADUATION AGREEMENT

538
00:28:29,980 --> 00:28:32,066
Mom, what is this?

539
00:28:32,149 --> 00:28:34,568
I would like for you
to sign that document.

540
00:28:34,652 --> 00:28:37,071
[Joon-su] Mom, you were serious
about graduating from marriage?

541
00:28:37,154 --> 00:28:40,407
[Hye-gyeong] We stay legally married,
but we live our lives separately.

542
00:28:40,491 --> 00:28:42,576
[Joon-su] Then how is that
any different from now?

543
00:28:42,660 --> 00:28:44,537
[Hye-gyeong] It's different to me!

544
00:28:45,287 --> 00:28:48,082
Read it over,
and then we'll go see a lawyer together.

545
00:28:48,666 --> 00:28:50,626
This is still a contract,
so we should do it properly.

546
00:28:50,709 --> 00:28:51,877
[sighs]

547
00:28:55,339 --> 00:28:56,757
[sighs]

548
00:28:59,468 --> 00:29:01,470
[sentimental music playing]

549
00:29:03,305 --> 00:29:05,432
You should have gone home
with Mom, you know?

550
00:29:06,725 --> 00:29:07,810
I still have work.

551
00:29:07,893 --> 00:29:10,980
[groans] Even I wouldn't want
a stone statue like you.

552
00:29:11,063 --> 00:29:14,233
You're so sweet to us,
so how can you do that to Mom?

553
00:29:14,858 --> 00:29:16,485
Because I'm afraid.

554
00:29:17,069 --> 00:29:18,070
Of what?

555
00:29:18,737 --> 00:29:22,116
With your children, it's a bond
that's meant to last through time.

556
00:29:23,450 --> 00:29:26,370
But the relationship with your spouse
can end at any moment.

557
00:29:27,079 --> 00:29:28,080
True.

558
00:29:28,664 --> 00:29:31,667
Plenty of people get married
and then divorced.

559
00:29:31,750 --> 00:29:32,960
Well, to me…

560
00:29:34,336 --> 00:29:36,463
it feels like walking through a minefield.

561
00:29:37,047 --> 00:29:38,048
A minefield?

562
00:29:41,427 --> 00:29:43,345
I'd say something without thinking,

563
00:29:43,887 --> 00:29:45,806
and if it struck a nerve with your mom,

564
00:29:45,889 --> 00:29:48,642
"Ah, I shouldn't bring that up again."

565
00:29:49,560 --> 00:29:51,604
So I avoid that topic next time.

566
00:29:52,187 --> 00:29:54,648
And then,
I'd struck another nerve and think,

567
00:29:55,399 --> 00:29:58,360
"This is a mine too.
I should avoid this as well."

568
00:29:58,444 --> 00:30:01,196
After doing everything I can to avoid it,

569
00:30:02,448 --> 00:30:04,074
I ended up clamming up entirely.

570
00:30:06,368 --> 00:30:08,912
I was just trying to keep
your mom's mind at ease,

571
00:30:10,372 --> 00:30:11,915
and it turned into a habit.

572
00:30:11,999 --> 00:30:13,459
So what now?

573
00:30:14,209 --> 00:30:15,878
What are you going to do, Dad?

574
00:30:17,004 --> 00:30:20,174
I don't think Mom was just saying that.

575
00:30:20,257 --> 00:30:22,301
It's a separation, not a divorce.

576
00:30:23,010 --> 00:30:24,637
That means I still have hope, right?

577
00:30:24,720 --> 00:30:26,055
[groans]

578
00:30:26,138 --> 00:30:27,264
Come on, Dad.

579
00:30:27,348 --> 00:30:29,433
For someone who looks so pessimistic,

580
00:30:29,516 --> 00:30:31,435
your thoughts are wildly optimistic.

581
00:30:31,518 --> 00:30:33,771
Is that an insult or a compliment?

582
00:30:33,854 --> 00:30:35,272
[scoffs]

583
00:30:35,856 --> 00:30:37,399
[both chuckling]

584
00:30:38,233 --> 00:30:39,401
Geez.

585
00:30:39,485 --> 00:30:42,404
Well, for now,
I'll just do what your mom wants

586
00:30:42,905 --> 00:30:44,323
and try to make it up to her.

587
00:30:44,406 --> 00:30:46,325
I'll buy her flowers

588
00:30:46,408 --> 00:30:47,993
and get her presents too.

589
00:30:48,952 --> 00:30:50,204
Did she say she likes palbochae?

590
00:30:50,287 --> 00:30:52,206
[chuckles] Mmm.

591
00:30:54,541 --> 00:30:57,127
[inhales sharply]
Then I'll treat her to that too.

592
00:30:59,546 --> 00:31:00,756
And you, Dad?

593
00:31:02,049 --> 00:31:05,928
Have you ever wanted to separate from Mom
since you got married?

594
00:31:09,765 --> 00:31:10,766
Sure, I have.

595
00:31:12,976 --> 00:31:14,978
On days when being together

596
00:31:15,729 --> 00:31:18,607
feels even lonelier
than if you were really alone,

597
00:31:20,025 --> 00:31:21,318
I definitely do.

598
00:31:24,363 --> 00:31:26,448
But my conclusion's always the same.

599
00:31:28,409 --> 00:31:30,077
I can't live without your mother.

600
00:31:30,828 --> 00:31:32,037
-[chuckles]
-[scoffs]

601
00:31:32,121 --> 00:31:33,997
[automated voice]
Bus number 38 is arriving soon.

602
00:31:34,081 --> 00:31:36,208
Mmm. I'm leaving. My bus is here now.

603
00:31:36,291 --> 00:31:38,669
Okay. Get home safe.

604
00:31:38,752 --> 00:31:39,753
Mmm.

605
00:31:39,837 --> 00:31:40,879
Oh.

606
00:31:40,963 --> 00:31:42,464
Is the cassette player working okay?

607
00:31:42,548 --> 00:31:44,216
Yeah, it's working fine.

608
00:31:44,299 --> 00:31:45,300
Good.

609
00:31:46,176 --> 00:31:47,970
That guy sure does solid work.

610
00:31:48,053 --> 00:31:48,887
[chuckles]

611
00:31:48,971 --> 00:31:50,139
I'm off.

612
00:31:59,732 --> 00:32:02,067
[Ji-yoon]
Why did you get divorced, Mr. Kang?

613
00:32:02,151 --> 00:32:04,945
-[sentimental music continues]
-Was it because you were lonely?

614
00:32:05,446 --> 00:32:07,573
Or because you made her lonely?

615
00:32:08,365 --> 00:32:10,117
Whatever the reason,

616
00:32:10,200 --> 00:32:12,578
is it something
that I'll be able to handle?

617
00:32:14,788 --> 00:32:16,415
[sighs heavily]

618
00:32:20,586 --> 00:32:22,463
[music fades]

619
00:32:23,172 --> 00:32:24,840
Hold on, let me get this straight.

620
00:32:24,923 --> 00:32:25,924
You're dating now?

621
00:32:26,008 --> 00:32:27,092
You told me to.

622
00:32:27,176 --> 00:32:28,260
But you said it'd be wrong.

623
00:32:28,343 --> 00:32:31,180
Well, I guess I must like
Ms. Ji-yoon enough to cross that line.

624
00:32:31,263 --> 00:32:32,389
[chuckles] "Ms. Ji-yoon"?

625
00:32:32,473 --> 00:32:33,974
Why are you so surprised?

626
00:32:34,057 --> 00:32:36,018
I'm just jealous, that's all.

627
00:32:36,101 --> 00:32:38,187
[mellow music playing on speakers]

628
00:32:43,233 --> 00:32:44,276
You like her that much?

629
00:32:44,860 --> 00:32:45,861
Mmm.

630
00:32:47,196 --> 00:32:48,947
She's just too good for me.

631
00:32:49,031 --> 00:32:51,742
Hey. Why do you keep going on
about how it's wrong

632
00:32:51,825 --> 00:32:53,160
and she's too good?

633
00:32:53,243 --> 00:32:54,828
What, is being divorced a crime now?

634
00:32:54,912 --> 00:32:57,831
No, it's not a crime,
but definitely a flaw.

635
00:32:57,915 --> 00:33:01,293
She probably needed a lot more
contemplating and courage than I did.

636
00:33:01,919 --> 00:33:05,005
When I think about that,
I can't afford to mess up.

637
00:33:06,089 --> 00:33:07,299
I don't want to hurt her at all.

638
00:33:08,342 --> 00:33:11,136
Kang Si-woo has finally become a man.

639
00:33:11,220 --> 00:33:12,679
And what was I all this time?

640
00:33:12,763 --> 00:33:14,223
A work machine.

641
00:33:14,306 --> 00:33:15,516
[scoffs]

642
00:33:16,099 --> 00:33:18,602
By the way, does Ms. Ji-yoon

643
00:33:18,685 --> 00:33:20,062
know it's Soo-jin?

644
00:33:22,189 --> 00:33:23,190
Mmm.

645
00:33:24,691 --> 00:33:25,818
[Seong-min] You're right.

646
00:33:26,819 --> 00:33:28,695
You really can't afford to mess this up.

647
00:33:29,738 --> 00:33:30,739
[chuckles]

648
00:33:33,200 --> 00:33:35,661
[intriguing music playing]

649
00:33:35,744 --> 00:33:38,705
[sighs] No matter how much I look at it,

650
00:33:38,789 --> 00:33:41,208
I can't get used to this new design.

651
00:33:41,291 --> 00:33:42,960
[Kee-tae] It might seem strange at first,

652
00:33:43,043 --> 00:33:44,837
but it gets prettier the more you look.

653
00:33:44,920 --> 00:33:46,964
What're you, the proud doting father?

654
00:33:47,464 --> 00:33:48,465
Of course.

655
00:33:49,424 --> 00:33:53,220
My kid might have a bit of a giant head,
but it's super smart.

656
00:33:53,303 --> 00:33:55,305
You can schedule it
for when you get off work,

657
00:33:55,389 --> 00:33:58,892
and it'll handle all the washing
and drying entirely on its own.

658
00:33:58,976 --> 00:34:01,979
It even sorts out
different fabric types effortlessly.

659
00:34:02,062 --> 00:34:04,898
[sighs] And boy,
does my kid spin fast. Mmm.

660
00:34:04,982 --> 00:34:07,901
Just take a short break,
and the whole wash-to-dry cycle is done.

661
00:34:07,985 --> 00:34:08,986
Oh!

662
00:34:09,570 --> 00:34:12,281
And our marketing angles,
that's all of them!

663
00:34:13,323 --> 00:34:15,993
I don't really know
what the right call is.

664
00:34:16,076 --> 00:34:17,411
[music fades]

665
00:34:17,494 --> 00:34:18,745
What do you mean by that?

666
00:34:18,829 --> 00:34:20,914
Functionality or aesthetics,

667
00:34:20,998 --> 00:34:22,416
which one should come first?

668
00:34:22,499 --> 00:34:24,251
There's no definitive standard.

669
00:34:24,334 --> 00:34:26,461
We can only refine our instincts
through experience.

670
00:34:26,545 --> 00:34:28,589
The problem is that

671
00:34:28,672 --> 00:34:30,716
aesthetics is highly subjective.

672
00:34:30,799 --> 00:34:33,218
Look how divided our opinions are
over one appliance.

673
00:34:33,302 --> 00:34:36,805
Then you must prioritize
universal consumer-centric values.

674
00:34:36,889 --> 00:34:39,224
If we're always led by consumers,

675
00:34:39,308 --> 00:34:40,976
then when will we ever lead the market?

676
00:34:44,438 --> 00:34:47,482
Oh! The refrigerator's here. [chuckles]

677
00:34:47,566 --> 00:34:49,568
[dolly rattling]

678
00:34:54,907 --> 00:34:56,033
Oh!

679
00:34:56,617 --> 00:34:59,494
The screen is smaller,
just like Ms. Cha suggested.

680
00:34:59,578 --> 00:35:02,164
-Yeah, and did you know about this?
-I didn't.

681
00:35:04,458 --> 00:35:06,084
Did you know about it, Mr. Kang?

682
00:35:06,752 --> 00:35:08,795
I knew the Design Team
held another meeting

683
00:35:08,879 --> 00:35:11,089
right after hearing
your feedback, Ms. Cha.

684
00:35:12,466 --> 00:35:15,594
Hmm. It looks brilliant design-wise too.

685
00:35:15,677 --> 00:35:18,221
[Si-woo] Yes, it's much better
than the first mock-up.

686
00:35:22,684 --> 00:35:24,019
-[phone beeps]
-[line rings]

687
00:35:24,102 --> 00:35:25,687
Yes, Counselor.

688
00:35:25,771 --> 00:35:29,483
Oh, well, if we leave now,
then we will arrive within an hour.

689
00:35:30,067 --> 00:35:31,360
[chuckles]

690
00:35:31,443 --> 00:35:33,987
I came to his shop
to make sure we go together.

691
00:35:35,489 --> 00:35:39,910
Well, he's willing to hear
what graduating from marriage means.

692
00:35:41,536 --> 00:35:43,413
Yes, yes, I'll do that.

693
00:35:43,914 --> 00:35:44,915
Okay.

694
00:35:57,010 --> 00:35:58,804
[exhales deeply]

695
00:36:09,231 --> 00:36:10,774
-[thudding]
-[Yeong-mook groans]

696
00:36:10,857 --> 00:36:12,567
-[screams]
-[groans]

697
00:36:12,651 --> 00:36:13,652
[Hye-gyeong] Honey!

698
00:36:14,152 --> 00:36:17,155
-Are you okay? Where does it hurt? Huh?
-[groans]

699
00:36:17,239 --> 00:36:18,532
-[gasps]
-Is it your ankle?

700
00:36:18,615 --> 00:36:19,992
-Your ankle? Huh?
-[groans]

701
00:36:21,284 --> 00:36:22,285
[sighs]

702
00:36:24,788 --> 00:36:26,790
[phone buzzing]

703
00:36:30,669 --> 00:36:31,670
Hi, Dad.

704
00:36:31,753 --> 00:36:33,255
What's up at this hour?

705
00:36:33,338 --> 00:36:36,174
[Yeong-mook] Well,
I took a little tumble down the stairs.

706
00:36:36,258 --> 00:36:37,592
What?

707
00:36:37,676 --> 00:36:38,677
And are you hurt?

708
00:36:38,760 --> 00:36:39,761
No.

709
00:36:39,845 --> 00:36:42,347
Uh, it's just a hairline fracture,
so I got a cast.

710
00:36:42,431 --> 00:36:45,726
Thing is, a customer's coming
to pick up something this evening.

711
00:36:46,309 --> 00:36:48,103
So maybe you can go and hand it to them.

712
00:36:48,186 --> 00:36:51,648
Then, on the door,
put a sign saying "Temporarily Closed."

713
00:36:51,732 --> 00:36:54,359
Okay, sure. Don't worry about that.

714
00:36:54,443 --> 00:36:56,403
Where are you right now?

715
00:36:56,486 --> 00:36:58,113
Are you alone up in the attic?

716
00:36:58,196 --> 00:36:59,239
Me? No.

717
00:36:59,322 --> 00:37:02,784
Your mom says if I try to go up there,
I would need surgery.

718
00:37:02,868 --> 00:37:04,911
[whispers] She was making
such a fuss about it.

719
00:37:05,454 --> 00:37:06,955
So I'm down in the living room right now.

720
00:37:07,039 --> 00:37:08,165
[tray slams]

721
00:37:08,248 --> 00:37:10,625
[whimsical music playing]

722
00:37:16,339 --> 00:37:17,549
Ji-yoon,

723
00:37:18,300 --> 00:37:21,887
I'd probably be better off
crawling up there, don't you think?

724
00:37:21,970 --> 00:37:23,096
No, Dad.

725
00:37:23,180 --> 00:37:26,141
This is a blessing in disguise.

726
00:37:26,224 --> 00:37:29,061
Turn a crisis into an opportunity?

727
00:37:29,144 --> 00:37:29,978
Mmm.

728
00:37:30,062 --> 00:37:32,981
Take this chance to rest up
and focus on Mom,

729
00:37:33,065 --> 00:37:33,899
got it?

730
00:37:33,982 --> 00:37:35,233
Okay.

731
00:37:35,942 --> 00:37:37,861
[gasps, sighs]

732
00:37:38,528 --> 00:37:41,573
Just my luck.
Of course my plan would backfire on me.

733
00:37:43,033 --> 00:37:44,409
[screams]

734
00:37:46,078 --> 00:37:47,579
[Yeong-mook sighs deeply]

735
00:37:49,247 --> 00:37:50,290
[music ends]

736
00:37:53,168 --> 00:37:54,961
Is everything okay with Mr. Cha?

737
00:37:55,045 --> 00:37:57,506
Yes, he fractured his leg.

738
00:37:57,589 --> 00:37:58,799
Is he all right?

739
00:37:58,882 --> 00:37:59,716
Yes.

740
00:38:01,051 --> 00:38:03,345
Uh, I need to stop by the store for him,

741
00:38:03,428 --> 00:38:04,805
so I'll be leaving early today.

742
00:38:06,181 --> 00:38:07,557
[sighs softly]

743
00:38:16,149 --> 00:38:17,734
-Do--
-May I please come with you?

744
00:38:18,235 --> 00:38:20,737
[tender music playing]

745
00:38:22,489 --> 00:38:23,490
Yes.

746
00:38:24,616 --> 00:38:26,868
I have something I'd like to ask you too.

747
00:38:28,995 --> 00:38:31,581
All right. We can talk on the way.

748
00:38:40,549 --> 00:38:41,883
[Si-woo inhales deeply]

749
00:38:42,551 --> 00:38:44,553
[music continues]

750
00:38:46,179 --> 00:38:48,265
You seem like you've been
in a bad mood all day.

751
00:38:49,307 --> 00:38:52,227
Well, my boss is giving me a hard time.

752
00:38:52,978 --> 00:38:54,104
[chuckles]

753
00:38:54,187 --> 00:38:55,856
He must be a mean boss,

754
00:38:55,939 --> 00:38:57,357
making things tough for you.

755
00:38:59,526 --> 00:39:02,779
You had something to say.
Was it to trash-talk your boss?

756
00:39:04,406 --> 00:39:05,407
Yes.

757
00:39:05,490 --> 00:39:06,867
Vent all you want.

758
00:39:06,950 --> 00:39:08,743
I'll join in with you on the trash talk.

759
00:39:14,749 --> 00:39:15,750
Last night--

760
00:39:15,834 --> 00:39:17,919
[phone ringing]

761
00:39:18,003 --> 00:39:19,045
MANAGER CHOI SOO-JIN

762
00:39:19,129 --> 00:39:21,047
[music fades]

763
00:39:22,924 --> 00:39:24,926
[ringing continues]

764
00:39:33,768 --> 00:39:34,978
You should take it.

765
00:39:37,647 --> 00:39:38,857
[ringing stops]

766
00:39:38,940 --> 00:39:40,483
Hello there, Ms. Choi Soo-jin?

767
00:39:41,526 --> 00:39:42,611
[person] Si-woo.

768
00:39:44,863 --> 00:39:46,907
Si-woo, how close are you?

769
00:39:47,490 --> 00:39:48,658
[Soo-jin] Mom!

770
00:39:48,742 --> 00:39:50,535
-Sorry. I'm hanging up now.
-[phone beeps]

771
00:39:50,619 --> 00:39:51,620
CALL ENDED

772
00:39:58,793 --> 00:40:00,962
[emotional music playing]

773
00:40:13,725 --> 00:40:16,144
TEMPORARILY CLOSED

774
00:40:21,024 --> 00:40:23,693
Was that Ms. Choi's mother?

775
00:40:25,654 --> 00:40:28,114
-Yes.
-[music fades]

776
00:40:28,657 --> 00:40:29,741
Is that why

777
00:40:29,824 --> 00:40:31,910
you two were in your car last night?

778
00:40:34,955 --> 00:40:37,457
The both of you looked
so serious in there,

779
00:40:37,958 --> 00:40:39,584
it felt uncomfortable saying hello.

780
00:40:42,796 --> 00:40:44,881
So I prodded you like a coward.

781
00:40:46,800 --> 00:40:47,842
I get it.

782
00:40:48,802 --> 00:40:50,720
It seems that I've lied to you.

783
00:40:52,764 --> 00:40:53,848
Yes.

784
00:40:57,394 --> 00:40:59,354
It bothered me all day long.

785
00:40:59,437 --> 00:41:01,940
I kept wanting to ask
what you two talked about.

786
00:41:03,024 --> 00:41:06,778
[sighs] But I had no idea
you'd still be in touch with her family.

787
00:41:07,529 --> 00:41:09,114
It was the first time actually.

788
00:41:11,491 --> 00:41:14,494
I guess I just have to
take your word for it, right?

789
00:41:17,497 --> 00:41:18,915
[Si-woo sighs]

790
00:41:22,669 --> 00:41:24,254
She has dementia.

791
00:41:26,464 --> 00:41:27,924
[melancholic music playing]

792
00:41:28,008 --> 00:41:29,718
In her mind, she's still

793
00:41:31,177 --> 00:41:32,470
ten years in the past.

794
00:41:35,974 --> 00:41:38,268
When we came back from the honeymoon,

795
00:41:38,351 --> 00:41:39,686
she looked at my husband…

796
00:41:42,647 --> 00:41:44,107
and asked me who he was.

797
00:41:45,525 --> 00:41:47,444
Then she asked me where you were.

798
00:41:50,238 --> 00:41:52,073
My mom's time is frozen

799
00:41:53,491 --> 00:41:56,077
right at the moment after we got married.

800
00:41:58,788 --> 00:42:00,832
I feel sorry for my husband.

801
00:42:03,501 --> 00:42:05,754
If she could just see you one last time,

802
00:42:05,837 --> 00:42:07,964
and say a final goodbye,

803
00:42:08,048 --> 00:42:10,592
I think she'll finally
stop looking for you.

804
00:42:11,176 --> 00:42:12,719
I know it's too much,

805
00:42:13,219 --> 00:42:15,263
but it's just one last favor.

806
00:42:18,516 --> 00:42:21,519
-[music continues]
-Why didn't you tell me from the start?

807
00:42:22,145 --> 00:42:23,563
Because I said no.

808
00:42:24,147 --> 00:42:25,357
And I didn't think

809
00:42:26,066 --> 00:42:28,360
sharing such deeply personal stories

810
00:42:28,443 --> 00:42:30,320
would be respectful
to the people involved.

811
00:42:30,403 --> 00:42:33,490
That means if I hadn't gotten
in your car today,

812
00:42:33,573 --> 00:42:34,949
I would've never known the truth.

813
00:42:37,160 --> 00:42:38,453
That's what I had hoped.

814
00:42:38,536 --> 00:42:39,537
Why?

815
00:42:41,247 --> 00:42:43,249
Is that your idea
of being considerate to me?

816
00:42:43,333 --> 00:42:44,376
Yes.

817
00:42:45,001 --> 00:42:48,421
Even if I could go back in time,
I wouldn't tell you.

818
00:42:49,005 --> 00:42:52,634
Because that's just my way
of showing you I care.

819
00:42:57,305 --> 00:42:58,723
[sighs heavily]

820
00:43:00,266 --> 00:43:01,351
I don't know.

821
00:43:03,061 --> 00:43:05,313
I think I would've hated it anyway…

822
00:43:07,065 --> 00:43:08,942
but I don't like knowing now either.

823
00:43:11,319 --> 00:43:13,363
Whatever decision that I make,

824
00:43:14,614 --> 00:43:15,657
trust me,

825
00:43:16,491 --> 00:43:18,034
it will be for your sake.

826
00:43:21,246 --> 00:43:23,039
Well, then please don't go.

827
00:43:27,210 --> 00:43:29,462
-Okay.
-[music fades]

828
00:43:30,755 --> 00:43:33,091
[emotional music playing]

829
00:43:38,221 --> 00:43:39,556
[Ji-yoon] If you were me,

830
00:43:40,181 --> 00:43:41,641
what would you have done?

831
00:43:47,647 --> 00:43:49,190
If you were me…

832
00:43:49,274 --> 00:43:51,025
[Si-woo] Then you should go and find out.

833
00:43:51,109 --> 00:43:52,861
Once you stop running from it,

834
00:43:53,361 --> 00:43:55,029
you'll understand what you really feel.

835
00:43:55,113 --> 00:43:57,615
If you need to talk more, please go ahead.

836
00:43:57,699 --> 00:43:59,033
I'll wait here.

837
00:44:00,285 --> 00:44:02,203
[Ji-yoon] …you would have
told me to go, right?

838
00:44:03,037 --> 00:44:05,331
You would've let me go,
saying you'd be waiting,

839
00:44:05,415 --> 00:44:06,749
never wavering.

840
00:44:07,375 --> 00:44:08,376
[panting]

841
00:44:11,129 --> 00:44:12,130
But…

842
00:44:13,506 --> 00:44:15,049
it's not that easy for me.

843
00:44:26,269 --> 00:44:28,229
[sighs]

844
00:44:28,313 --> 00:44:29,898
[phone buzzes]

845
00:44:35,820 --> 00:44:36,905
Hello, Ji-yoon.

846
00:44:37,572 --> 00:44:39,574
[sighs] You should go.

847
00:44:42,285 --> 00:44:43,328
Ji-yoon.

848
00:44:44,496 --> 00:44:46,498
The thing is, if you don't go,

849
00:44:46,581 --> 00:44:48,708
she might reach out to you again.

850
00:44:49,709 --> 00:44:50,960
I'd really hate that.

851
00:44:52,045 --> 00:44:55,715
So go and settle it once and for all.

852
00:45:00,011 --> 00:45:01,012
However,

853
00:45:02,180 --> 00:45:03,723
there's no next time.

854
00:45:04,557 --> 00:45:05,558
All right.

855
00:45:06,476 --> 00:45:07,685
Thank you.

856
00:45:10,772 --> 00:45:11,856
As for Hye-ji's wedding…

857
00:45:11,940 --> 00:45:13,733
I'll make sure I'm not late.

858
00:45:15,235 --> 00:45:16,236
Okay.

859
00:45:16,778 --> 00:45:18,321
I'll be waiting for you.

860
00:45:27,956 --> 00:45:29,290
[sighs]

861
00:45:30,416 --> 00:45:31,417
[sighs]

862
00:45:33,962 --> 00:45:36,798
You're really done with group blind dates?

863
00:45:36,881 --> 00:45:37,757
Mm-hmm.

864
00:45:37,840 --> 00:45:40,843
I'm tired of going there, trying to find
a safe middle ground with them.

865
00:45:40,927 --> 00:45:43,346
And I hate saying things
I don't even mean too.

866
00:45:43,930 --> 00:45:45,974
So what kind of person
do you want to date?

867
00:45:46,057 --> 00:45:47,141
Hmm…

868
00:45:47,642 --> 00:45:51,521
Someone I can be completely real with
and still feel truly safe.

869
00:45:52,188 --> 00:45:53,731
[cries]

870
00:45:58,736 --> 00:45:59,737
[Jae-in] Excuse me.

871
00:45:59,821 --> 00:46:02,031
But I've fallen for your daughter
at first sight.

872
00:46:02,615 --> 00:46:05,368
It's about riding the rolling waves
and having fun.

873
00:46:06,202 --> 00:46:08,288
Doing what you want without being scared,

874
00:46:08,788 --> 00:46:09,831
isn't that enjoying life?

875
00:46:09,914 --> 00:46:12,417
You are Goo-won's cousin, right?

876
00:46:12,500 --> 00:46:13,668
Hi, I'm Lee Jae-in.

877
00:46:13,751 --> 00:46:15,420
No-ah's new best, uh…

878
00:46:16,045 --> 00:46:17,046
boyfriend.

879
00:46:17,130 --> 00:46:21,050
[in French] Would you be my boyfriend?

880
00:46:21,801 --> 00:46:24,095
Oh, yes, I'd like that.

881
00:46:25,346 --> 00:46:26,347
[chuckles]

882
00:46:26,931 --> 00:46:27,932
[in English] What?

883
00:46:28,433 --> 00:46:30,560
You've already met that person.

884
00:46:31,644 --> 00:46:32,645
Haven't you?

885
00:46:34,272 --> 00:46:35,273
[Na-ri sighs]

886
00:46:37,775 --> 00:46:40,445
Have you been to that new restaurant
right out front?

887
00:46:41,029 --> 00:46:42,113
No.

888
00:46:42,196 --> 00:46:44,699
Apparently, it's amazing.
People line up all through lunch.

889
00:46:44,782 --> 00:46:48,328
-Did you see the guy with the purple hair?
-Yeah, I did. He's so cute, it's crazy.

890
00:46:48,411 --> 00:46:49,871
Do you think he has a girlfriend?

891
00:46:52,248 --> 00:46:53,249
What is it?

892
00:47:06,262 --> 00:47:07,263
[gasps]

893
00:47:10,224 --> 00:47:11,225
Yikes.

894
00:47:12,101 --> 00:47:13,186
I should get going.

895
00:47:13,269 --> 00:47:14,729
-Bye.
-Uh.

896
00:47:35,708 --> 00:47:37,251
Why did you suddenly cut off contact?

897
00:47:37,919 --> 00:47:39,337
I thought I made you uncomfortable.

898
00:47:39,921 --> 00:47:41,547
Then why show up out of nowhere now?

899
00:47:42,590 --> 00:47:44,467
I couldn't bear it any longer.

900
00:47:44,550 --> 00:47:46,260
[sighs]

901
00:47:47,261 --> 00:47:49,138
Did you really mean it
when you asked me out?

902
00:47:50,723 --> 00:47:51,724
Mmm.

903
00:47:52,475 --> 00:47:54,143
I still can't trust you yet.

904
00:47:55,895 --> 00:47:57,313
Let me earn your trust.

905
00:47:57,897 --> 00:47:59,273
And you're too young.

906
00:48:01,109 --> 00:48:03,111
I can't do anything about that.

907
00:48:08,449 --> 00:48:10,660
I'm going to nag you
if you get hard to reach.

908
00:48:12,578 --> 00:48:15,081
I don't want you getting friendly
with other girls either.

909
00:48:16,290 --> 00:48:17,291
Yeah.

910
00:48:17,375 --> 00:48:18,751
I'll stay easy to reach.

911
00:48:19,335 --> 00:48:21,003
And I won't get close to any other girls.

912
00:48:24,716 --> 00:48:28,094
[in French] Would you be my boyfriend?

913
00:48:30,346 --> 00:48:32,098
[sighs]

914
00:48:41,482 --> 00:48:43,401
[in English] Why aren't you answering?

915
00:48:48,156 --> 00:48:49,157
Mmm.

916
00:48:51,117 --> 00:48:52,410
Are you crying?

917
00:48:53,494 --> 00:48:54,746
[Jae-in breathes shakily]

918
00:48:54,829 --> 00:48:56,581
[gasps] Wh-Why are you crying?

919
00:48:57,415 --> 00:49:00,001
I don't know. I'm just so happy.

920
00:49:00,668 --> 00:49:03,629
I was super scared
I might never see you again.

921
00:49:05,548 --> 00:49:06,758
[chuckles]

922
00:49:14,223 --> 00:49:15,933
Look, if you don't respect me,

923
00:49:16,642 --> 00:49:18,436
then I won't respect you either.

924
00:49:19,604 --> 00:49:20,605
Mmm.

925
00:49:21,814 --> 00:49:23,274
In a relationship,

926
00:49:24,066 --> 00:49:26,152
I'm still going to put myself first.

927
00:49:26,819 --> 00:49:27,820
[inhales sharply]

928
00:49:29,781 --> 00:49:30,782
Mmm.

929
00:49:31,783 --> 00:49:33,534
If your love fades away…

930
00:49:36,537 --> 00:49:38,498
I will leave without forgiving you.

931
00:49:39,832 --> 00:49:40,833
Mmm.

932
00:49:45,797 --> 00:49:47,173
That's how I'll love you.

933
00:49:49,509 --> 00:49:51,010
I hope you'll do the same for me.

934
00:49:52,094 --> 00:49:53,095
Mmm.

935
00:49:54,347 --> 00:49:55,348
[chuckles]

936
00:50:03,022 --> 00:50:05,024
[joyful music playing]

937
00:50:07,026 --> 00:50:09,028
[singing in French]

938
00:50:42,937 --> 00:50:44,105
[song ends]

939
00:50:48,359 --> 00:50:50,236
Oh. Uh. [chuckles]

940
00:50:51,487 --> 00:50:53,072
-[in English] Hi.
-[Young-hun chuckles]

941
00:50:53,155 --> 00:50:55,533
Mr. Lee, what brings you
into the office on the weekend?

942
00:50:55,616 --> 00:50:58,744
Uh, I thought we should expand
the range of identifiable ingredients.

943
00:50:59,662 --> 00:51:00,955
And you, you work weekends?

944
00:51:01,038 --> 00:51:04,500
I have flexible working hours.
I left early yesterday to pick up my kids.

945
00:51:04,584 --> 00:51:06,919
-[chuckles]
-Got your hands full, huh? [chuckles]

946
00:51:07,003 --> 00:51:09,380
I'll just grab some files
and head to the product showroom.

947
00:51:09,463 --> 00:51:11,340
-Carry on.
-Yeah. Good luck.

948
00:51:11,424 --> 00:51:12,425
[Young-hun] Good luck.

949
00:51:14,051 --> 00:51:15,052
Okay.

950
00:51:15,553 --> 00:51:17,221
-[chuckles] Good luck.
-Right.

951
00:51:17,305 --> 00:51:19,932
-[exclaims, laughs]
-[chuckles]

952
00:51:26,772 --> 00:51:27,607
HANKUK UNIVERSITY START-UP "NIKKE"!

953
00:51:27,690 --> 00:51:30,151
[ominous music playing]

954
00:51:30,234 --> 00:51:32,403
KANG SI-WOO, LEE SEONG-MIN,
JIN SEUNG-HYEON, PARK BEOM-SU

955
00:51:40,661 --> 00:51:41,662
LEE SEONG-MIN

956
00:51:46,125 --> 00:51:47,585
[music fades]

957
00:51:48,294 --> 00:51:50,004
CHECK THE ONE ITEM REMOVED

958
00:51:52,089 --> 00:51:53,132
[sighs]

959
00:51:55,217 --> 00:51:57,595
CHECK THE INGREDIENTS INSIDE
ADDED (1), REMOVED (0)

960
00:51:57,678 --> 00:51:59,931
[chuckles] This is fun.

961
00:52:00,014 --> 00:52:03,309
-[ominous music resumes]
-That may be a good enough software bug.

962
00:52:05,353 --> 00:52:06,854
What should I tweak next?

963
00:52:08,272 --> 00:52:09,148
Ah.

964
00:52:09,231 --> 00:52:12,735
CHECK THE INGREDIENTS INSIDE
ADDED (1), REMOVED (0)

965
00:52:14,612 --> 00:52:16,614
[music fades]

966
00:52:22,078 --> 00:52:23,079
Mom.

967
00:52:33,381 --> 00:52:34,590
Mom,

968
00:52:34,674 --> 00:52:35,675
Si-woo's here.

969
00:52:38,302 --> 00:52:40,137
[sighs, chuckles]

970
00:52:40,221 --> 00:52:41,430
Si-woo!

971
00:52:43,057 --> 00:52:44,350
Have you been well?

972
00:52:44,976 --> 00:52:46,060
Yeah.

973
00:52:47,186 --> 00:52:48,187
-Soo-jin.
-Hmm?

974
00:52:48,270 --> 00:52:49,981
Go get Si-woo a nice warm cup of tea.

975
00:52:50,064 --> 00:52:51,315
Sure.

976
00:52:51,399 --> 00:52:52,400
Have a seat.

977
00:52:54,777 --> 00:52:55,778
Thank you.

978
00:53:03,577 --> 00:53:05,287
Why is your mom so hard to get a hold of?

979
00:53:05,371 --> 00:53:06,789
Did something happen?

980
00:53:07,331 --> 00:53:09,458
No, nothing happened.

981
00:53:09,542 --> 00:53:10,751
Then what is it?

982
00:53:11,335 --> 00:53:12,962
Did I upset her somehow?

983
00:53:13,713 --> 00:53:17,466
You see, you kids need to start preparing
for your studies abroad.

984
00:53:18,676 --> 00:53:22,680
Maybe she missed your call
because she's busy preparing all that.

985
00:53:22,763 --> 00:53:24,807
[chuckles]

986
00:53:24,890 --> 00:53:26,350
I still find it amazing.

987
00:53:26,934 --> 00:53:29,270
Your mom and I promised to become in-laws

988
00:53:29,353 --> 00:53:31,439
ever since you two were little kids,

989
00:53:31,522 --> 00:53:33,315
and that's exactly what happened.

990
00:53:33,858 --> 00:53:35,609
What are the odds that two best friends

991
00:53:35,693 --> 00:53:38,404
from the same high school
would have children

992
00:53:38,487 --> 00:53:42,241
raise them together, and later in life
walk down the aisle together

993
00:53:42,324 --> 00:53:44,452
-as in-laws? [chuckles]
-[melancholic music playing]

994
00:53:45,036 --> 00:53:46,746
It truly felt like a dream.

995
00:53:49,373 --> 00:53:53,419
And Si-woo, darling, you looked so handso…

996
00:54:06,557 --> 00:54:08,350
And who are you?

997
00:54:10,019 --> 00:54:11,103
Mother?

998
00:54:16,984 --> 00:54:20,738
I must really resemble…

999
00:54:22,782 --> 00:54:25,201
your mother quite a lot.

1000
00:54:46,180 --> 00:54:47,598
[music ends]

1001
00:54:47,681 --> 00:54:49,266
-I'll see you later. Okay.
-Bye!

1002
00:54:49,350 --> 00:54:51,143
Hye-ji looks so beautiful today,
don't you think?

1003
00:54:51,227 --> 00:54:53,270
-Right?
-I can't wait for the wedding.

1004
00:54:53,938 --> 00:54:55,147
[Ji-yoon] Are you on your way?

1005
00:54:55,731 --> 00:54:58,317
[camera shutter clicking]

1006
00:54:58,400 --> 00:54:59,401
[Hye-ji] Ji-yoon.

1007
00:54:59,902 --> 00:55:01,946
PARK BEOM-SU

1008
00:55:04,156 --> 00:55:06,158
[inhales deeply, sighs]

1009
00:55:10,830 --> 00:55:13,124
[intriguing music playing]

1010
00:55:15,376 --> 00:55:16,877
-Huh?
-[Beom-su] College sweethearts,

1011
00:55:16,961 --> 00:55:19,213
married and studying abroad.
Are you enjoying life?

1012
00:55:19,296 --> 00:55:21,549
If you're jealous, you lose, but…

1013
00:55:24,969 --> 00:55:26,220
What's this?

1014
00:55:29,390 --> 00:55:30,391
[Soo-jin] Thank you.

1015
00:55:30,474 --> 00:55:32,852
-[music fades]
-It must've been hard for you to do this.

1016
00:55:33,519 --> 00:55:35,396
I guess she feels like she…

1017
00:55:36,272 --> 00:55:37,982
she owes you emotionally.

1018
00:55:38,774 --> 00:55:39,775
Mmm.

1019
00:55:42,403 --> 00:55:44,613
Once she moves into the care facility,

1020
00:55:44,697 --> 00:55:46,198
I won't need to contact you.

1021
00:55:47,324 --> 00:55:49,326
Though Mom will probably ask
about you. [chuckles]

1022
00:55:49,910 --> 00:55:51,704
I don't think I can do this again either.

1023
00:55:53,414 --> 00:55:56,208
I want to do right by the person
I'm seeing right now.

1024
00:55:56,292 --> 00:55:58,085
Oh, so you're seeing someone?

1025
00:55:58,711 --> 00:55:59,795
I had no idea.

1026
00:56:00,588 --> 00:56:02,173
Gosh, I'm sorry.

1027
00:56:02,256 --> 00:56:03,674
She'd be upset if she found out.

1028
00:56:03,757 --> 00:56:05,092
I told her earlier.

1029
00:56:05,676 --> 00:56:06,844
That's good.

1030
00:56:09,722 --> 00:56:11,473
Kang Si-woo, you've really changed.

1031
00:56:12,766 --> 00:56:14,185
The old you would've tried

1032
00:56:14,768 --> 00:56:16,896
to solve everything all on your own.

1033
00:56:19,648 --> 00:56:21,567
Is she the reason for this sudden change?

1034
00:56:24,486 --> 00:56:25,487
Mmm.

1035
00:56:26,405 --> 00:56:28,115
I wonder what kind of girl she is.

1036
00:56:31,785 --> 00:56:32,995
[footsteps running]

1037
00:56:33,078 --> 00:56:35,039
The woman you were with just collapsed!

1038
00:56:35,706 --> 00:56:36,749
[Soo-jin gasps]

1039
00:56:41,003 --> 00:56:42,254
You look so pretty.

1040
00:56:42,838 --> 00:56:44,423
Hey. Where's your boyfriend?
He's still not here?

1041
00:56:44,506 --> 00:56:46,634
Ah. He's running a little late.

1042
00:56:46,717 --> 00:56:47,676
Why?

1043
00:56:47,760 --> 00:56:50,012
Something came up at work.

1044
00:56:50,095 --> 00:56:52,348
Oh. Make sure I meet him before you leave.

1045
00:56:52,431 --> 00:56:53,432
Mmm.

1046
00:56:53,933 --> 00:56:57,603
[sighs] My friend,
you're officially a grown-up, huh?

1047
00:56:57,686 --> 00:56:59,271
-You're a mom…
-[exclaims]

1048
00:56:59,355 --> 00:57:01,065
…and now you're getting married too.

1049
00:57:01,148 --> 00:57:03,192
-[exclaims]
-This is crazy.

1050
00:57:03,275 --> 00:57:05,444
I'm actually super nervous right now.

1051
00:57:05,527 --> 00:57:07,655
This small wedding isn't small at all.

1052
00:57:07,738 --> 00:57:08,948
Uh-uh-uh.

1053
00:57:09,031 --> 00:57:10,950
[sighs] Maybe I shouldn't have
agreed to this.

1054
00:57:11,033 --> 00:57:13,619
What's this?
Lee Hye-ji is actually nervous?

1055
00:57:13,702 --> 00:57:15,746
[Hye-ji sighing]

1056
00:57:16,747 --> 00:57:17,748
Ji-yoon.

1057
00:57:17,831 --> 00:57:19,083
Mm-hmm?

1058
00:57:19,166 --> 00:57:22,253
I told Ga-eul about it the other day.

1059
00:57:22,336 --> 00:57:23,587
What?

1060
00:57:24,255 --> 00:57:25,464
Your boyfriend's past.

1061
00:57:26,966 --> 00:57:28,550
I'm sorry. I'm so, so sorry.

1062
00:57:28,634 --> 00:57:31,553
[groans] I made a terrible mistake.

1063
00:57:32,763 --> 00:57:33,889
It's okay.

1064
00:57:34,807 --> 00:57:37,726
It's the truth,
and I never intended to hide it anyway.

1065
00:57:37,810 --> 00:57:41,981
Hey, you have to stop
if it ever gets too hard, okay?

1066
00:57:42,064 --> 00:57:45,150
Please don't think about anyone else.
Focus on yourself.

1067
00:57:45,234 --> 00:57:47,027
Mmm. Okay.

1068
00:57:47,820 --> 00:57:50,281
But now, you're the star of the day,

1069
00:57:50,364 --> 00:57:51,865
so I'll say that to you.

1070
00:57:51,949 --> 00:57:53,909
-Hmm?
-Hye-ji,

1071
00:57:53,993 --> 00:57:55,869
your happiness always comes first.

1072
00:57:55,953 --> 00:57:58,330
Before your husband or your baby. Got it?

1073
00:57:59,957 --> 00:58:02,209
-[chuckles] Are you crying?
-No, I can't! [laughs]

1074
00:58:02,293 --> 00:58:04,169
-Hey, don't make me cry.
-[chuckles]

1075
00:58:04,253 --> 00:58:05,379
I can't cry already.

1076
00:58:05,462 --> 00:58:06,463
-[both laugh]
-[MC] Next up,

1077
00:58:06,547 --> 00:58:09,300
the bride's friends will be performing
the wedding song.

1078
00:58:09,383 --> 00:58:11,010
Please give them a warm round of applause.

1079
00:58:21,145 --> 00:58:23,939
-You said Ji-yoon's boyfriend was coming.
-I guess he's running late.

1080
00:58:24,732 --> 00:58:25,983
Because he's so busy, right?

1081
00:58:26,066 --> 00:58:27,067
[sighs]

1082
00:58:27,151 --> 00:58:29,069
Just pretend you don't know, will you?

1083
00:58:30,529 --> 00:58:31,905
[Ga-eul] Hye-ji,

1084
00:58:32,990 --> 00:58:35,868
-congrats on your wedding!
-[Seung-jun] Congrats, Hye-ji.

1085
00:58:41,332 --> 00:58:43,334
[slow music playing]

1086
00:58:57,139 --> 00:59:00,934
[Ga-eul, in Korean]
♪ Maybe, back at the very beginning ♪

1087
00:59:01,018 --> 00:59:04,021
♪ It was as if time had stopped ♪

1088
00:59:04,104 --> 00:59:07,524
♪ It was like you had walked ♪

1089
00:59:07,608 --> 00:59:10,486
♪ From a place in an unknown land ♪

1090
00:59:10,569 --> 00:59:13,864
♪ Like the welcome snow ♪

1091
00:59:13,947 --> 00:59:17,409
♪ At the dawn of early winter ♪

1092
00:59:17,493 --> 00:59:20,371
♪ That hurried into autumn ♪

1093
00:59:20,454 --> 00:59:23,749
♪ You came to me ♪

1094
00:59:23,832 --> 00:59:27,503
♪ Your bright smile ♪

1095
00:59:27,586 --> 00:59:30,381
♪ Is exactly what I love ♪

1096
00:59:30,464 --> 00:59:33,050
♪ But sometimes ♪

1097
00:59:33,133 --> 00:59:35,719
♪ The sad look I see in your eyes ♪

1098
00:59:35,803 --> 00:59:40,057
♪ Weighs on my heart ♪

1099
00:59:40,140 --> 00:59:42,309
♪ I want to know ♪

1100
00:59:42,393 --> 00:59:46,772
♪ Everything about you
Even the smallest things ♪

1101
00:59:46,855 --> 00:59:48,857
♪ But for some reason ♪

1102
00:59:48,941 --> 00:59:53,654
♪ You don't ever tell me ♪

1103
00:59:53,737 --> 00:59:55,864
♪ If that's the case ♪

1104
00:59:55,948 --> 01:00:00,953
♪ I will visit you in your dreams
When you're asleep at night ♪

1105
01:00:01,036 --> 01:00:06,166
♪ And quietly listen to your story ♪

1106
01:00:07,626 --> 01:00:11,630
♪ Quietly listen to ♪

1107
01:00:12,840 --> 01:00:16,760
♪ Your story ♪

1108
01:00:16,844 --> 01:00:19,096
[music fades]

1109
01:00:20,431 --> 01:00:22,391
[foot tapping]

1110
01:00:22,474 --> 01:00:24,977
[tense music playing]

1111
01:00:26,562 --> 01:00:29,982
[Young-sam, in English] Dig into
Kang Si-woo and find his weakness.

1112
01:00:37,197 --> 01:00:39,199
[sighs]

1113
01:00:42,077 --> 01:00:44,079
[Kee-tae] I need you to be
my secret confidante.

1114
01:00:45,539 --> 01:00:47,666
This is too heavy to keep to myself.

1115
01:00:53,380 --> 01:00:55,048
-[music fades]
-[Ga-eul] Ji-yoon!

1116
01:01:01,263 --> 01:01:03,807
What's wrong? Did something happen?

1117
01:01:03,891 --> 01:01:05,517
No, nothing.

1118
01:01:08,270 --> 01:01:09,271
Is it because of him?

1119
01:01:10,898 --> 01:01:12,232
What are you trying to do?

1120
01:01:13,192 --> 01:01:14,860
I just want you to be happy,

1121
01:01:15,527 --> 01:01:18,197
but right now you don't look happy at all.

1122
01:01:23,285 --> 01:01:26,205
I heard he was married once.

1123
01:01:26,830 --> 01:01:28,749
And to the mentor you always talked about.

1124
01:01:29,791 --> 01:01:30,792
So what?

1125
01:01:30,876 --> 01:01:33,337
You chose to leave me,
so choose someone better.

1126
01:01:33,420 --> 01:01:34,963
He'll only make your life difficult.

1127
01:01:35,047 --> 01:01:36,423
Why choose such a difficult path?

1128
01:01:36,507 --> 01:01:38,050
Hey, Cho Ga-eul.

1129
01:01:38,133 --> 01:01:39,676
I'm not trying to get back together.

1130
01:01:39,760 --> 01:01:40,761
I just…

1131
01:01:42,387 --> 01:01:43,847
I just want you to stop seeing him.

1132
01:01:43,931 --> 01:01:45,599
Hey, watch what you're saying.

1133
01:01:45,682 --> 01:01:46,934
You're being incredibly rude.

1134
01:01:50,687 --> 01:01:53,273
You're crossing the line, Mr. Cho Ga-eul.

1135
01:01:53,357 --> 01:01:55,609
You're not good enough for Ji-yoon.

1136
01:01:55,692 --> 01:01:57,945
She deserves
to be with someone much better.

1137
01:01:58,028 --> 01:02:00,155
That's for Ms. Ji-yoon to decide.

1138
01:02:00,781 --> 01:02:03,033
Besides, you have no right to say that.

1139
01:02:03,116 --> 01:02:04,076
I do have the right.

1140
01:02:07,829 --> 01:02:08,830
I am her…

1141
01:02:10,290 --> 01:02:11,291
longtime friend.

1142
01:02:12,000 --> 01:02:13,001
No.

1143
01:02:14,628 --> 01:02:16,797
If this is your idea of being friends,

1144
01:02:17,297 --> 01:02:18,465
I won't do it.

1145
01:02:19,508 --> 01:02:20,509
Never.

1146
01:02:29,226 --> 01:02:30,936
[breathes shakily]

1147
01:02:31,937 --> 01:02:34,439
[tender music playing]

1148
01:02:42,239 --> 01:02:44,074
You said you were

1149
01:02:45,367 --> 01:02:46,952
going to be here on time.

1150
01:02:48,620 --> 01:02:50,038
Yes, but something came up.

1151
01:02:51,248 --> 01:02:53,500
In that case,
you shouldn't have come at all.

1152
01:02:55,460 --> 01:02:56,962
You just ended up

1153
01:02:58,171 --> 01:03:01,174
hearing things
that you really didn't need to hear.

1154
01:03:02,342 --> 01:03:03,719
Don't worry, I'm fine.

1155
01:03:04,803 --> 01:03:06,847
It just upsets me that you had to

1156
01:03:07,431 --> 01:03:08,724
listen to such things.

1157
01:03:11,518 --> 01:03:13,061
[sighs] Today,

1158
01:03:14,521 --> 01:03:16,773
I saw an old photo of the two of you.

1159
01:03:20,569 --> 01:03:22,654
You were smiling so beautifully…

1160
01:03:25,073 --> 01:03:26,533
and I hated that.

1161
01:03:29,286 --> 01:03:31,163
I know it was a long time ago,

1162
01:03:31,246 --> 01:03:33,498
and it has nothing to do with me now,

1163
01:03:35,083 --> 01:03:36,752
but it still broke my heart.

1164
01:03:37,961 --> 01:03:38,962
Ji-yoon.

1165
01:03:39,588 --> 01:03:42,257
I thought that I would be able
to handle this well…

1166
01:03:44,635 --> 01:03:46,970
but I guess I was just fooling myself.

1167
01:03:47,054 --> 01:03:50,349
Please don't keep it to yourself
and imagine things.

1168
01:03:51,808 --> 01:03:53,602
Tell me whatever
is making it hard for you.

1169
01:03:54,311 --> 01:03:55,312
Yes.

1170
01:03:57,356 --> 01:03:58,774
It is hard.

1171
01:04:01,652 --> 01:04:04,363
Seeing you with Ms. Choi
having meetings at work,

1172
01:04:05,113 --> 01:04:07,783
or waiting for you
while you meet with her family,

1173
01:04:08,867 --> 01:04:12,954
and not being able to properly tell anyone
that we're together, is very difficult.

1174
01:04:14,206 --> 01:04:16,166
But the hardest part is

1175
01:04:17,959 --> 01:04:19,920
that I walked into all of this

1176
01:04:20,921 --> 01:04:22,464
knowing everything,

1177
01:04:23,048 --> 01:04:24,966
so I'm the only one to blame.

1178
01:04:31,390 --> 01:04:32,391
I'm sorry.

1179
01:04:36,937 --> 01:04:38,438
The choices I made

1180
01:04:38,939 --> 01:04:40,899
have ended up affecting you, Ji-yoon.

1181
01:04:42,275 --> 01:04:43,860
I'm deeply sorry about that.

1182
01:04:45,487 --> 01:04:46,780
[Ji-yoon] I can't believe

1183
01:04:46,863 --> 01:04:50,075
the first sorry I hear from Mr. Kang
is something like this.

1184
01:04:50,575 --> 01:04:51,702
I knew it.

1185
01:04:52,828 --> 01:04:55,288
-I just hate love.
-[sighs]

1186
01:04:55,372 --> 01:04:57,374
[music continues]

1187
01:05:00,127 --> 01:05:02,963
You're offering me an apology
for something I can't forgive.

1188
01:05:03,964 --> 01:05:06,216
But all you can give is forgiveness.

1189
01:05:10,679 --> 01:05:11,680
[inhales sharply]

1190
01:05:13,765 --> 01:05:14,766
[sighs]

1191
01:05:15,934 --> 01:05:18,437
It would've been better
to know nothing from the start.

1192
01:05:18,937 --> 01:05:20,272
If I hadn't known,

1193
01:05:20,814 --> 01:05:23,108
I could've just liked you
without any worries

1194
01:05:23,191 --> 01:05:24,693
and let it run its course.

1195
01:05:25,777 --> 01:05:27,529
[Ji-yoon] I hurt him with words

1196
01:05:28,113 --> 01:05:29,614
I should not say,

1197
01:05:30,115 --> 01:05:33,160
hoping that they cut
as painfully as possible

1198
01:05:33,243 --> 01:05:34,911
in that very moment.

1199
01:05:34,995 --> 01:05:38,081
The thing is that the more I like you,

1200
01:05:39,791 --> 01:05:43,253
the smaller I become,
you know what I mean?

1201
01:05:46,298 --> 01:05:49,634
Tell me, how come I have to bear
the weight of your past too?

1202
01:05:50,218 --> 01:05:52,345
[Ji-yoon] Back then, and even now,

1203
01:05:53,013 --> 01:05:55,599
the one who wears me out the most…

1204
01:05:55,682 --> 01:05:56,892
I'm sorry…

1205
01:05:59,144 --> 01:06:01,396
I'm sorry that
I'm not as strong as you are.

1206
01:06:19,164 --> 01:06:20,624
[Ji-yoon] …has always been…

1207
01:06:23,126 --> 01:06:24,211
me.

1208
01:06:36,556 --> 01:06:39,768
SPECIAL THANKS TO NAM KEE-AE

1209
01:06:41,061 --> 01:06:42,979
[tender music continues]

1210
01:07:07,087 --> 01:07:08,964
[Seong-min] You need to be
a little different than usual.

1211
01:07:09,047 --> 01:07:11,174
[Na-ri] Doesn't Mr. Kang look
totally handsome today?

1212
01:07:11,258 --> 01:07:12,092
Did you find the answer?

1213
01:07:12,175 --> 01:07:13,760
[Si-woo] I can't change the past,

1214
01:07:13,844 --> 01:07:16,096
but I can change the present,
don't you think?

1215
01:07:16,179 --> 01:07:17,013
Ah!

1216
01:07:17,097 --> 01:07:18,974
[Jae-in] Don't treat me like a child.

1217
01:07:19,057 --> 01:07:20,767
About the guy
who fixed my cassette player…

1218
01:07:20,851 --> 01:07:23,854
He's a good kid. And a lonely one too.

1219
01:07:24,437 --> 01:07:29,317
Can you tell me why you and Ms. Choi
decided to divorce?

1220
01:07:29,401 --> 01:07:31,236
[Kee-tae] There's something
between these two.

1221
01:07:31,319 --> 01:07:32,487
[Young-sam] Found it.

1222
01:07:33,113 --> 01:07:34,447
[Young-hun] Ruining the demo would…

1223
01:07:34,531 --> 01:07:35,907
[Ji-yoon] What on earth is all this?

1224
01:07:35,991 --> 01:07:37,367
Did someone hack the system?

